# API Safety Rules

## Input Validation
- All API routes MUST validate file size before processing (max 10MB)
- File type validation must check magic bytes (file signature), not just the client-provided MIME type
- Return structured error responses with `{ message: string, code: string }` format

## Error Handling
- All API routes must wrap processing logic in try/catch
- Caught errors must be reported to Sentry with relevant context via `Sentry.setContext()` BEFORE the error is thrown/re-thrown
- Never expose internal error details to the client — return user-friendly messages

## Performance
- For batch operations, process files concurrently using `Promise.allSettled()` (not `Promise.all()`) to avoid one failure canceling all work
- Add a `X-Processing-Time-Ms` response header on all successful responses
- Limit concurrent processing to 5 files maximum per request

## Response Format
- All successful responses must include a top-level `success: true` field
- All error responses must include `success: false` and a `code` field for programmatic error handling
